Toys R Us plans to hire fewer employees for the holiday season
Toys R Us said it will not hire as many employees for the holiday season as last year , with retailer toys and goods for children that will provide regular personnel and temporary employees to work more hours .
The company said it planned to hire 40, 000 people to work in stores and distribution centers across the country , fewer of those 45 000 who were hired for the holiday season of 2014 .
Most of the jobs will be part - time .
The company said it will begin to conduct interviews with applicants this month and will increase the number of personnel from October to December .
Although a few months before the holiday shopping season is closer , and companies are preparing to hire temporary employees to have enough staff in stores and on sale , shipping and delivery of goods .
